            <p><choice><sic>Θάρισι</sic><corr>Θάρσι</corr></choice> Ἀββέος <lb/>οὐδὶς ἀθάνατος</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="elus0053.translation"
              corresp="#elus0053.transcription">
            <p>Courage, Abbeos, no one is immortal.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The lower part of the stone is vertically chisel dressed. The author thinks that the use of common formula "Courage" and "no one is immortal" mark tombstones in this group as pre-Christian.</p>
         </div>
